overview.note: "The votes of four towns, we are informed, were lost, on account of informality in the returns." Connecticut Centinel (Norwich, CT). October 29, 1805.
The Connecticut Journal (New Haven, CT) lists Aaron Austin with 10644 votes, Andrew Hull, Jr. with 7674 votes, Hezekiah Goodrich with 7186 votes and Samuel Whittelsey with 6941 votes.
The Connecticut Herald (New Haven, CT) lists Aaron Austin with 10644 votes and Andrew Hull, Jr. with 7674 votes.

sub_unit.name: Norwich
sub_unit.note: "At the election on Monday, the highest number of votes for Assistant on the Federal Ticket was 123 and on the Republican 49." The Courier (Norwich, CT). September 18, 1805.
